Parliament, Tuesday, 12 March 2019 – A joint meeting of the Standing and Select Committees on Appropriations will tomorrow conduct public hearings on the 2019 Public Audit Excess Bill [B7 - 2019]. The Bill is to provide that the specified excess of the audit fee of certain categories of organs of state, payable to the Auditor-General, as envisaged in the Public Audit Act, 2004, is, if the stated conditions are complied with, a direct charge against the National Revenue Fund; and to provide for matters connected therewith. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 13 March 2019
	Time: 09:00 am 
	Venue: Committee Room M46, Ground Floor, Marks Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE STANDING AND SELECT COMMITTEES ON APPROPRIATIONS, MS YVONNE PHOSA AND MR CHAREL DE BEER. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact: Name: Felicia Lombard
